Description: Foot and lower wall fragment of Ionian pottery bowl; flaring ring foot; interior glazed with traces of added colour line; exterior reserved save lowest part of wall and outside of foot; underside reserved; graffito under foot.
Bibliographic references: Johnston 2006a / Trademarks on Greek Vases: Addenda (East Greek 225)
Villing et al 2013-2015 / Naukratis: Greeks in Egypt (GG.1182)
